choices.text:
by walk, bike, bus or car. Depending on the weather, the mood, the distance, I take alternative ways. For example, if it’s a windy day and I do not have any special errand to do, I risk taking my bike on the road. But on rainy days I rather choose to walk or take the bus. In either ways, the source of pollution is small! Nevertheless, between heavy traffic and bad weather, I will most likely always prefer a car-free activity.

Having a car-free lifestyle is not about giving up on the activities I already love and slowing down, but rather about an opportunity to discover alternative ones.

Soccer: Getting muddy, scoring on bottom of the net, The Euro Cup 2012

Reading: Spending hours with head in a book, Kids chapter books, Beautiful cover design

Dance: Getting sweaty, Smilling on the music, Latin rhythm

Which activities do we only do with the car?

My main concern about considering car-free plan as best practices is the risk of completely stepping away from car’s way of doing things. I am referring to the activities that sounds like this:

“Ugh, this bus goes one stop less than demands the route planner. I should just take the car instead. That would be faster and more totally awesome. ”
